{"id":84836,"title":"[Panniculitides in an internist's practice].","abstract":"By panniculitides is meant a group of heterogeneous inflammatory diseases characterized by the involvement of subcutaneous adipose tissue. A diversity of their forms and variants of their course determines the need for careful patent examination to verify the diagnosis. The lecture gives a diagnostic algorithm and outlines principles in the differential diagnosis of panniculitides and its treatment approaches in current clinical practice.","date":"2014-07-16","categories":"Pathological Conditions and Signs and Symptoms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25026808","annotations":[{"name":"Disease","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Differential diagnosis","weight":0.782659,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_diagnosis"},{"name":"Adipose tissue","weight":0.777392,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adipose_tissue"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.768313,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Internal medicine","weight":0.765521,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal_medicine"},{"name":"Inflammation","weight":0.762559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inflammation"},{"name":"Tissue (biology)","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tissue_(biology)"},{"name":"Subcutaneous tissue","weight":0.668375,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subcutaneous_tissue"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.642761,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Algorithm","weight":0.276698,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithm"},{"name":"Patent","weight":0.20545,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patent"},{"name":"Homogeneity and heterogeneity","weight":0.120845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homogeneity_and_heterogeneit